HEADWORD: Crepane
<hw>Cre"pane</hw> <pr>(kr?"p?n)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>crepare</ets> to crack.]</ety> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>An injury in
a horse's leg, caused by the shoe of one hind foot striking and cutting
the other leg. It sometimes forms an ulcer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

